<header>
	Read the writing task on the left and look at the list of ideas on the right that a group of IELTS students produced. Decide whether each idea is an argument for an international language, an argument against or an idea which is irrelevant to the task.
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="leftFloat" src="../media/LC_AW_022.JPG" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  <br/>
  <ol id="questionList">
    <br/>
    <li id="q1">Cost of teaching everyone the language <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a1">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a2">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a3">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q2">Diversification of language into dialects <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a4">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a5">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a6">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q3">Help international trade <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a7">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a8">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a9">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q4">Improve international co-operation and understanding <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a10">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a11">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a12">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q5">Interpreters and translators would lose their jobs <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a13">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a14">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a15">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q6">Make international travel easier <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a16">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a17">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a18">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q7">Many languages already have a large number of words in common <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a19">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a20">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a21">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q8">Many people enjoy learning new languages <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a22">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a23">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a24">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q9">Might not be used <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a25">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a26">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a27">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q10">Reduce nationalism <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a28">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a29">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a30">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q11">Reduce the amount of translation work needed <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a31">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a32">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a33">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q12">Simplify electronic communication <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a34">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a35">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a36">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q13">There are about 6,000 languages spoken in the world today <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a37">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a38">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a39">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q14">World would lose cultural diversity <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a40">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a41">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a42">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q15">Would kill less widely-spoken languages <list class="answerList"><li><a id="a43">Argument for</a></li><li><a id="a44">Argument against</a></li><li><a id="a45">Irrelevant idea</a></li></list><br/></li>
